*** DEADLINE APRIL 21 NOON ***
EE16B is looking for lab assistants, readers, and all kinds of TAs! If you are interested in joining course staff next semester, please fill out this form. We will hold interviews after the form deadline. If you have any questions/concerns, you can email Jessie Yang (email on 16B course website) or comment on this post.
Here are some great reasons to join course staff for EE16B:
- It's a great way to give back to the series. The course could not run without our wonderful readers and lab assistants (as you all well know because everyone complains about lack of lab staff).
- Being a lab assistant is a crucial part in the success of the course because the labs are such an important part of the series. You will attend a 2-hr training each week and then assist in lab for ~ 3-hrs a week. By assisting, you sharpen your EE lab skills and gain a deeper understanding of the course material.
- Being a reader is a great way to keep up with the content, working with TAs on debugging assignments as well as grading.
- Being a reader or lab assistant is the first step to becoming a TA for the course in the future!
- As a TA, you learn how to teach and improve your leadership. You also get to explore the material more by leading sections and/or creating course content.
- It's a great way to keep using your EE knowledge and work with hands-on projects (robot car!!!)
- You'll get P/NP course units or paid!
The only prereq is that you've taken EE16B or EE20/40.
Thanks!!
Hope you join the 16B fam :)
history.subject: JOIN EE16B COURSE STAFF FALL 2017!!
